---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Trust Center"
  description="Security, privacy, and operational overview for Pixelated Empathy."
>
  <section class="brutalist-section py-20">
    <div class="site-shell site-shell--narrow">
      <h1 class="brutalist-heading text-4xl md:text-6xl mb-6">Trust Center</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mb-10">
        Pixelated Empathy is being built for sensitive training workflows. This
        page describes the areas we focus on most when teams ask about security,
        privacy, and operational controls.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="brutalist-card">
          <h3 class="brutalist-subheading mb-3">Privacy</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            Transcript handling, retention choices, and review workflows are
            product decisions, not just policy footnotes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="brutalist-card">
          <h3 class="brutalist-subheading mb-3">Security</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            We design around encryption, access control, auditability, and
            deployment choices that fit more sensitive environments.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="brutalist-card">
          <h3 class="brutalist-subheading mb-3">Operational Review</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            Teams evaluating the platform can ask for documentation and discuss
            the controls they need before rollout.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="brutalist-card mt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
          Common evaluation topics
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
          <li>Encryption and key management expectations</li>
          <li>Retention, export, and deletion workflows</li>
          <li>Access control for supervisors, trainees, and administrators</li>
          <li>Deployment requirements for more regulated environments</li>
        </ul>
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex mt-6 brutalist-button brutalist-button--primary"
        >
          Request security information
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
